net.fathomsoft.nova.tree

Class BinaryOperation

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.Node
      • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.Value
        • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.IValue
          • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.BinaryOperation

  • public class BinaryOperation
extends IValue
    Node extension that represents the use of a binary operator. For example: "153 + 4 / 2" represents two binary operator nodes. The first node consists of the "153" as the left hand value, and the binary node "4 / 2"

      • decodeStatement

        public static Value decodeStatement(Node parent,
                                    java.lang.String statement,
                                    Location location,
                                    boolean require)
        Decode the given statement into a BinaryOperation if possible. If it is not possible, the method will return null. The requirements of a BinaryOperation include: Contains an operator such as '!=', '>=', '<=', '>', '<', '*', '/', '+', '-', and '%' surrounded by two comparable values.

        Example inputs include:
        • 5 / 2
        • (a.getWidth() + b.getHeight) / array.getSize()
        • variableName % 2 == 0
        The last two examples contain two BinaryOperations.
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent of the current statement.
        statement - The statement to translate into a BinaryOperation if possible.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        Returns:
        The generated Node, if it was possible to translated it into a BinaryOperation.
